             <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: =
16px; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;"><b>You said a fe=
w days ago you want to work with Elon Musk and Vivek Ramaswamy on DOGE, and=
 find some ways to cut government spending or inefficiencies. Have you talk=
ed to Elon Musk directly about this? And what are some areas of agreement y=
ou could come to with them as a Democrat?</b><br/><br/>I=E2=80=99ve known E=
lon for 15 years. I=E2=80=99ve texted back and forth with him, and I=E2=80=
=99ve talked to him on and off for years. One thing to point out: Obama hel=
ped Elon disrupt the defense industry when it came to the rocket launches. =
Boeing had a monopoly with Lockheed Martin on launching rockets to put sate=
llites up in space, and <b>Ash Carter</b> and Barack Obama said, <i>Elon, y=
ou can do it cheaper?</i> <i>Fine. We=E2=80=99re going to let you bid.</i> =
He had rockets that were reusable, [which is] the way he underbid Boeing an=
d Lockheed. And today, the American
taxpayers have saved money because of Obama=E2=80=99s collaboration with El=
on Musk and getting SpaceX to do that. <br/><br/><b>So the <i>opposite</i> =
of what Biden did by stiff-arming Elon and Tesla on that E.V. summit.</b><b=
r/><br/>Biden should have invited him. I don=E2=80=99t understand why he di=
dn=E2=80=99t. When Obama gave the E.V. loan to Tesla, we should have insist=
ed on labor neutrality in that loan. We didn=E2=80=99t, and that was a miss=
=2E I=E2=80=99m for Tesla allowing unioniz=
ation, and Elon knows that. He know=
s we have a disagreement. But you don=E2=80=99t disinvite him; you invite h=
im and you make the case. You don=E2=80=99t say, like Biden did, that [Gene=
ral Motors C.E.O.] <b>Mary Barra</b> started the electric vehicle revolutio=
n. That would be like saying that <b>Isaac</b> <b>Newton</b> didn=E2=80=99t=
 start calculus or something. I mean, it=E2=80=99s just wrong! So I think t=
hat was gratuitously insulting. <br/><br/>With DOGE, what I would look for =
is where we can get rid of the grip of the five aerospace and
defense primes, and help make the defense department more efficient. Let=E2=
=80=99s get rid of some of the excess profits of defense contractors. That =
would be enormous. It=E2=80=99s 56 percent of the budget! Or, what if they =
come up with a way to automatically populate tax returns? That would be gre=
at. That=E2=80=99s an idea Democrats have been pushing. The point is to sup=
port policies where they will help the American people and oppose them wher=
e they won=E2=80=99t. If they go after Social Security, obviously I=E2=80=
=99ll oppose that with every fiber of my being. We should be for <i>increas=
ing</i> Social Security benefits. Or if they try to dismantle funding for t=
he C.F.P.B., I would oppose that completely. The C.F.P.B. is saving money f=
or many consumers with credit card fees and mortgage fees. <br/><br/>So let=
=E2=80=99s not just reflexively oppose making government more efficient. If=
 they=E2=80=99re going after agencies that are genuinely duplicative and th=
ere=E2=80=99s waste, then we should be forward-looking at that.
<b>F.D.R.</b> in his New Deal speech said, we don=E2=80=99t want wasteful g=
overnment spending. Obama talked about that. What Bernie says is, we=E2=80=
=99re spending money, not wasting money. We have to show that government ca=
n be effective, and also that we=E2=80=99re the party that=E2=80=99s willin=
g to cut wasteful spending.<br/><br/><b>Last thing, what=E2=80=99s the next=
 step for you? You are a unique voice, at least right now. What do you want=
 to do if you don=E2=80=99t see a voice like this in the Democratic primary=
 in four years? Would you run?</b><br/><br/>You=E2=80=99re basically asking=
 the president question in a different way. <br/><br/><b>Yeah, duh.</b><br/=
><br/>I want to build the economic platform, not just for the Democratic Pa=
rty, but for the country. My father came to this country in 1968, to Michig=
an, and it was the time when we were about to go to the moon. America was t=
he place to do big things. It was a country that was the manufacturing and =
technology superpower of the world. We had this vibrant
middle class. I want that vision for America where the technology we have, =
in A.I. and biotechnology, doesn=E2=80=99t just help a few zip codes. That =
we mobilize all of our people to be the best manufacturer in the world, to =
have economic vitality in every part of the country.<br/><br/>I believe tha=
t I have studied enough American history and talked to enough people in com=
munities to have a concrete solution of how we do that. I also know some of=
 the extraordinary people who are working on those things to bring that vis=
ion to life. And whoever ends up being in positions of power, I=E2=80=99d s=
ay, please plagiarize my ideas. I want this platform to succeed. It=E2=80=
=99s fundamentally what I think the country needs, and what role I will hav=
e in all of that is=E2=80=A6 who knows? That=E2=80=99s for people to decide=
=2E <br/></td>
